Inspection Summary

  • Inspection type: Comprehensive Chimney Inspection
  • Purpose of Inspection: To assess the structural integrity and safety of chimneys in conveying smoke and combustion gases to the exterior.
  • Deficiencies Violated: DEFICIENCY 1 � OUTSIDE: A VISUALLY ACCESSIBLE CHIMNEY, FLUE, OR FIREBOX CONNECTED TO A FIREPLACE OR WOOD-BURNING APPLIANCE IS INCOMPLETE OR DAMAGED SUCH THAT IT MAY NOT SAFELY CONTAIN FIRE AND CONVEY SMOKE AND COMBUSTION GASES TO THE EXTERIOR., DEFICIENCY 2 � OUTSIDE: CHIMNEY EXHIBITS SIGNS OF STRUCTURAL FAILURE.
  • Overall Findings: The inspection revealed significant structural damage and safety concerns with the outside chimneys, including incomplete or damaged structures that may not safely contain fire and convey smoke, as well as signs of structural failure posing an imminent danger of collapse. Immediate repairs are necessary to ensure safety.

Deficiencies

Source

NSPIRE-Standard-Chimney_20230811.pdf

Detailed Findings

Deficiency:DEFICIENCY 1 � OUTSIDE: A VISUALLY ACCESSIBLE CHIMNEY, FLUE, OR FIREBOX CONNECTED TO A FIREPLACE OR WOOD-BURNING APPLIANCE IS INCOMPLETE OR DAMAGED SUCH THAT IT MAY NOT SAFELY CONTAIN FIRE AND CONVEY SMOKE AND COMBUSTION GASES TO THE EXTERIOR.

  • Title: CHIMNEY
  • Violation: Yes
  • Description: The deficiency in the Image_data matches the location (outside) and the description of structural instability and damage in the chimney, including missing and dislodged bricks, crumbling mortar, and deteriorated cement which affect the chimney's ability to convey smoke and combustion gases safely.
  • Recommendation: Urgent repair is recommended to restore the structural integrity of the chimney and ensure it can safely convey smoke and combustion gases to the exterior.
  • HCV_fail_Pass: Fail
  • HCV_correction_timeframe: 24 hours
  • Severity: Life-Threatening
  • Criteria_in_policy_document: A visually accessible chimney, flue, or firebox connected to a fireplace or wood-burning appliance is incomplete or damaged such that it may not safely contain fire and convey smoke and combustion gases to the exterior.

Deficiency:DEFICIENCY 2 � OUTSIDE: CHIMNEY EXHIBITS SIGNS OF STRUCTURAL FAILURE.

  • Title: CHIMNEY
  • Violation: Yes
  • Description: The deficiency in the Image_data shows significant structural damage to the chimney located outside, which aligns with the criteria of structural failure such as misaligned bricks and imminent danger of collapse mentioned in the context.
  • Recommendation: Immediate structural assessment and repair are necessary to prevent potential collapse and ensure safety.
  • HCV_fail_Pass: Fail
  • HCV_correction_timeframe: 24 hours
  • Severity: Life-Threatening
  • Criteria_in_policy_document: The chimney exhibits signs of structural failure such that the integrity of the chimney is jeopardized.

Deficiency:DEFICIENCY 1 � UNIT: A VISUALLY ACCESSIBLE CHIMNEY, FLUE, OR FIREBOX CONNECTED TO A FIREPLACE OR WOOD-BURNING APPLIANCE IS INCOMPLETE OR DAMAGED SUCH THAT IT MAY NOT SAFELY CONTAIN FIRE AND CONVEY SMOKE AND COMBUSTION GASES TO THE EXTERIOR.

  • Title: CHIMNEY
  • Violation: No
  • Description: The deficiency in the Image_data is related to structural damage to chimneys located outside, whereas this deficiency pertains to units inside and their ability to safely contain fire and convey smoke. There is no correlation between the location and type of deficiency in the Image_data and this deficiency.
  • Recommendation: Not Applicable
  • HCV_fail_Pass: Fail
  • HCV_correction_timeframe: 24 hours
  • Severity: Life-Threatening
  • Criteria_in_policy_document: A visually accessible chimney, flue, or firebox connected to a fireplace or wood-burning appliance is incomplete or damaged such that it may not safely contain fire and convey smoke and combustion gases to the exterior.

  • Title: CHIMNEY
